22/11/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The police arrested on Friday (November 20th) another suspect for the murder of a French football fan in Belgrade two months ago.
The suspect, identified as Deyan S., 39, is the 11th person detained in relation to the incident.
Brice Taton, 28, a fan of French football club Toulouse, died in hospital on September 28th, after he was attacked by fans of rival team Partizan Belgrade ahead of a match between the two squads.
His death sparked a wave of protests in Serbia against violence.
(B92, AP, Blic, Beta - 20/11/09)
